  "text": "Contents\n\nContents\n\nNote: T HERE ARE T HOUSANDS of worlds, all different from ours.\n\n1 C AT C HANT A DMIRED his elder sister Gwendolen. She was a witch.\n\n2 C AT WAS A LARMED by Miss Larkins. She was the daughter of Mr. Larkins at the junk shop.\n\n3 T HE T RAIN J OURNEY lasted about an hour, before the train puffed into Bowbridge. . .\n\n4 T HE S AME S OFTNESS and silence were there when the red-haired Mary woke Cat. . .\n\n5 G WENDOLEN R EFUSED TO tell Cat what she was going to do.\n\n6 G WENDOLEN G AVE V ENT to her fury in her room after dinner.\n\n7 I T R AINED ON Saturday afternoon. Gwendolen shut herself into her room. . .\n\n8 G WENDOLEN W ENT D OWN to the village to get her dragons’ blood on Wednesday afternoon.\n\n9 B Y T HIS T IME , Cat was as bewildered as the strange girl seemed to be. Chant?\n\n10 C AT W ATCHED H IS moment and, when Mr. Saunders called them to lessons. . .\n\n11 B Y THE T IME Janet had laced both her boots, Cat was sure it was lunchtime.\n\n12 C HRESTOMANCI’S S TUDY WAS a large, sun-filled room with books in shelves. . .\n\n13 T HEY WERE U SHERED into a private parlor in the White Hart.\n\n14 C AT S CREAMED . Flames burst out of him all over. He screamed again. . .\n\n15 I T WAS A G LORIOUS start-of-autumn day, with everything green and gold, hot and still.\n\n16 “C AT,” SAID C HRESTOMANCI , from almost behind Cat’s head. “Cat!”\n\nHarperCollins e-book Exclusive Extras:\n Who Is Chrestomanci?\n\nAbout Dressing Gowns\n\nRelated Worlds\n\nTypes of Magic\n\nChrestomanci Castle\n\nThe Importance of Cats\n\nThe Willing Warlock\n\nOneir\n\nTonino\n\nThe Worlds of Diana Wynne Jones: An Interview\n\nA BOUT THE A UTHOR\n\nB OOKS BY D IANA W YNNE J ONES\n\nC REDITS\n\nA BOUT THE P UBLISHER\n\nC OPYRIGHT",
